{
  "texts": [
    "When tools are invoked, their outputs are written back into the respective agent's memory (5)(6), thus closing the CoT [27] (Planning).",
    "In addition, ChatDRex can incorporate optional safeguard layers.",
    "Input guardrails mitigate prompt injection risks before queries reach the LLM (2), while output guardrails constrain generated responses to domain-specific requirements and filter potentially hallucinatory content (7) [32].",
    "These safeguards are not fixed components of every agent but can be activated depending on the task.",
    "This selective integration allows the system to balance robustness against computational efficiency in a fine-grained manner."
  ]
}